    <h2>BWH - BushWise Sites Administration Login</h2>
    <h3>The portal to all things wonderful:</h3>
    <p>
    Enter your assigned <b>Username</b> and <b>Password</b> then click the Login button. Depending on your User permissions, upon a successful Login you will be presented with your choice of areas to visit and / or administer.
    </p>
    <form id='vLogin'
    onsubmit='return formCheck()' 
     onreset='return formClear()' 
      action='mail.cgi'
      method='post'>
    <fieldset class='sm'>
      <label for='uname'><span class='req'>Username:</span></label>
      <input type='text' id='uname' name='mv_username' value='' size='24' maxlength='64' class='txtInput' />
      <label for='pwrd'><span class='req'>Password:</span></label>
      <input type='password' id='pwrd' name='mv_password' value='' size='24' maxlength='64' class='txtInput' />
      <br />
      <button type='submit' value='Login' name='mv_click'>Login</button>
      <button type='reset'>Clear Form</button>
    </fieldset>
    </form>
    <h4>Further Information regarding Log-Ins:</h4>
    <p>
    In the event of problems, please go to the <a href='contact.html' title='Contact Us'>contact page</a> and let us know what your problem is. We do not offer a &#8220;Remember Me&#8221; option ( utilising Cookies ) for Logins as this is a security risk if a non authorised person uses your machine without your knowledge. Please do not ask us to <i>fix</i> this as it is not broken nor overlooked and is a deliberate security feature. Thank you.
    </p>
    <h4>Accountability and Responsibility...</h4>
    <p>
    Please be aware that <b>each and every</b> action that you do / take whilst in the administration area is recorded creating a time-stamped <i>audit trail</i>. This means that we can account for all actions taken on our servers and present an accurate record of &#8220;who did what, and when&#8221;. This is for everyone's benefit to highlight who is responsible for any changes made at any time<sup>1</sup>.
    </p>
    <span class='smTxt'>
      1: This includes any edits or changes that BushWise staff make, &#8220;fair's fair&#8221;. 
    </span>
